The paper discusses future research directions in information theory, which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions inputs from experts in fields such as genomics, biology, economics, and neuroscience, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to subcategories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
